parameters: Young Atu: Agonia, are you really leaving the army!?

Young Agonia: Yes, I have met someone who will teach me many
things that I should do.

Young Atu: Hmm... the chaos of war is still far from
settling down.

Young Atu: I wish the fun days of rampaging through the
empire, crushing bandits and monsters, would continue...

Young Agonia: Ahaha, it's just like you, Atu. Your bravery
is rumored even within the Imperial Army.

Young Agonia: Eventually, I hope you encounter not only
worthy enemies but also people deserving of your respect,
Atu.

Young Atu: You always say complicated things! Well, I'll
just casually climb the ranks within the army.

Young Atu: Because it seems like I can have more interesting
battles over there!

Atu and Agonia participated in the First Tarasa War on the
side of the Empire. Atu, who grew up on the island, excelled
in naval warfare and became a soldier who saved many
soldiers in dire situations, attracting attention.

The two of them remained in the Imperial Army even after the
war, and they raced through the chaotic post-war period. Atu
fearlessly charged into enemy lines, trampling over the
enemies. Agonia, on the other hand, calmly hunted down the
enemies, deliberately preparing escape routes.

Although they were complete opposites in every way, they
fought together and achieved great results. The Imperial
Army could not ignore their contributions, and just after
rumors of their promotion began to circulate, Agonia
confessed that she would be leaving the army.

Atu hesitated for a moment about whether to stop Agonia's
decision. However, he quickly reconsidered, thinking that it
would be rude to stop his best friend's determination.
Besides, Atu was confident that they would meet again
somewhere.

And so, Agonia headed towards the adventurer's guild where
the great widow resides. Atu, on the other hand, chose to
continue fighting in the Imperial Army.

For Atu, battle was the ultimate form of self-expression.
Therefore, he could view battle not as a means, but as an
end in itself. He fought not to advance in rank, but to rank
up in order to fight.

However, there was a major pitfall in that aesthetic. There
were significant entanglements in terms of career
advancement, and even more so when it came to politics. Atu
was not aware that he had stepped into that world.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Fotizona Guard: Are you from the Guild? Please don't take
away our jobs too much, okay?

Fotizona Guard: Dragon Slayer! It is an honor to be able to
converse with the hero of the empire.
